    <aside class="panel">
      <h3 style="margin-top:0">How it works</h3>
      <div class="muted">The Lens monitors text as you type and uses a set of lightweight heuristics to flag places where intent could be unclear or tone misunderstood. It then offers friendly micro-actions.</div>

      <div style="height:12px;"></div>

      <div class="visual">
        <!-- Replace the image path below with a URL if needed -->
        <img src="/mnt/data/A_pitch_deck_image_for_a_communication_tool_design.png" alt="mock" style="max-width:100%; max-height:100%; border-radius:8px;" />
      </div>

      <div style="height:12px;"></div>

      <div>
        <h4 style="margin-bottom:6px;">Common Flags</h4>
        <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:8px;">
          <div class="flag"><div class="icon" style="background:#ef4444">!</div><div><div class="title">Intent unclear</div><div class="desc">Message doesn't clearly state the desired action or timeline.</div></div></div>
          <div class="flag"><div class="icon" style="background:#f59e0b">⚠</div><div><div class="title">Potentially blunt</div><div class="desc">Wording that may read as abrupt to some recipients.</div></div></div>
          <div class="flag"><div class="icon" style="background:#10b981">✓</div><div><div class="title">Vague timing</div><div class="desc">Phrases like "when you have a sec" or "ASAP" are ambiguous.</div></div></div>
        </div>
      </div>

